commentary: Vettori to Sarfraz Ahmed, no run slower through the air, Sarfraz goes for a sweep and the ball lobs up into the keeper's gloves. Vettori and Ronchi are certain about this. Umpire Raza just stands there, unimpressed. So New Zealand go for a review. The ball certainly deflected off the heel and into Ronchi's hands. I wonder if there is glove though... Very difficult to judge. Can they look at a leg-before, because Sarfraz was in front of all three stumps here. Had a giant stride forward though. Tense, tense, tense decision for third umpire Joel Wilson. Looks like he decides there was no glove. Onto the lbw then, Umpire's call on the leg-before, even with a decent chunk of the ball hitting leg stump...

commentary: Milne to Sarfraz Ahmed, 1 run 146kph, short and Sarfraz has struck the pull quite well to deep midwicket. Seven runs off the over.

commentary: McClenaghan to Sarfraz Ahmed, OUT taken by Ronchi! Just about! Sarfraz is gone and it's a Mitch that turns a match again. Cross-seamed short ball that followed Sarfraz as he moved outside leg to make room for himself. Goes for a pull on instinct and top-edges it straight up. The rest was taken care of by an alert Ronchi
